'''阿瑟·格雷格·苏兹伯格'''（{{lang-en|Arthur Gregg Sulzberger}}，{{bd|1980年|8月5日}}）是美国的一名[[记者|记者]]，也是《[[纽约时报|纽约时报]]》的发行人。作为发行人，监督着作为该公司的报道机关的新闻和事业运营。<ref>{{cite news |title=On Trust and Transparency: A.G. Sulzberger, Our New Publisher, Answers Readers' Questions |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2018/01/22/reader-center/ag-sulzberger-publisher-reader-questions.html |access-date=2020-07-14 |work=The New York Times |date=2018-01-22 |archive-date=2020-11-09 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201109014343/https://www.nytimes.com/2018/01/22/reader-center/ag-sulzberger-publisher-reader-questions.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>索尔兹伯格主导该公司向数字化过渡，并主导订户第一主义的政策。<ref>{{cite journal |last1=Pompeo |first1=Joe |title="The Time Will Come When This Is a Digital-Only News Organization": A.G. Sulzberg, Sam Dolnick, and David Perpich Open Up About Succession, Trump, and the Eventual End of Print |journal=Vanity Fair |date=2018-10-09 |url=https://www.vanityfair.com/news/2018/10/new-establishment-summit-new-york-times |access-date=2020-07-14 |archive-date=2021-02-08 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210208235446/https://www.vanityfair.com/news/2018/10/new-establishment-summit-new-york-times |dead-url=no }}</ref>继父亲[[小阿瑟·苏兹伯格|小阿瑟·苏兹伯格]]之后<ref name=NewYork-DeputyEditorAnalysis-2016>{{cite news |last=Levitz |first=Eric |title=A.G. Sulzberger Vanquishes Cousins, Becomes Deputy Publisher of New York Times |url=http://nymag.com/daily/intelligencer/2016/10/a-g-sulzberger-becomes-deputy-publisher-of-new-york-times.html |work=[[New_York_(magazine)|New York]] |date=2016-10-19 |accessdate=2021-02-14 |archive-date=2018-07-09 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180709064726/http://nymag.com/daily/intelligencer/2016/10/a-g-sulzberger-becomes-deputy-publisher-of-new-york-times.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>，预定2018年1月1日接任发行人<ref>{{cite journal |last1=Klein |first1=Julia M. |title=Public Enemy No 1 |journal=Brown Alumni Magazine |date=2019-07-08 |url=https://www.brownalumnimagazine.com/articles/2019-07-08/public-enemy-no-1 |access-date=2020-07-14 |publisher=Brown University |archive-date=2020-10-23 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201023035223/https://www.brownalumnimagazine.com/articles/2019-07-08/public-enemy-no-1 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=A·G·苏兹伯格将接任《纽约时报》出版人|url=https://cn.nytimes.com/business/20171215/a-g-sulzberger-new-york-times-publisher/|access-date=2021-09-01|author=SYDNEY EMBER|date=2017-12-18|last=|first=|work=纽约时报中文网|language=zh|archive-date=2022-03-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220318113742/https://cn.nytimes.com/business/20171215/a-g-sulzberger-new-york-times-publisher/|dead-url=no}}</ref>，2021年1月1日，接任该公司的董事长<ref name="reuters20200924">{{cite news|url=https://jp.reuters.com/article/uk-new-york-times-sulzberger-idUKKCN26E3IG|title=NYT's Sulzberger Jr to retire as chairman by end of December|work=ロイター|date=2020-09-24|accessdate=2020-12-25}}</ref>。为了避免和父亲的名字混淆，将首字母“A・G”作为名称。<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nikkei.com/article/DGXLASGN19H2X_Q6A021C1000000|title=NYタイムズ、A・G・サルツバーガー氏を副発行人に指名|work=日本経済新聞|date=2016-10-20|accessdate=2020-12-26|language=ja|archive-date=2017-02-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170205170627/http://www.nikkei.com/article/DGXLASGN19H2X_Q6A021C1000000/|dead-url=no}}</ref>

